---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'El Salvador Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/el-salvador/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Guatemala for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/guatemala' },
  { title: 'Nicaragua for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/nicaragua' },
  { title: 'Costa Rica for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/costa-rica' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'esFit', header: 'El Salvador Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$350-500/mo', esFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$410-585/mo', esFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$315-450/mo', esFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$290-415/mo', esFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$250-380/mo', esFit: 'Budget' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$315-500', annual: '$3,780-6,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$430-665', annual: '$5,160-7,980' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$580-895', annual: '$6,960-10,740' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: '$40-100/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: '$200-500/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in El Salvador 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in El Salvador. Dollar economy, Bitcoin adoption, improving safety, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in El Salvador"
  subheadline="El Salvador offers US dollar currency, Bitcoin adoption, Pacific beaches, improving safety, and affordable living—Central America's emerging destination with unique financial advantages."
  heroImage="/images/countries/el-salvador-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose El Salvador</h2>
  <p>
    El Salvador offers US dollar as currency (no exchange risk), Bitcoin as legal tender, Pacific beaches, affordable living, and dramatically improved safety under current policies. For those seeking dollarized economy and willing to embrace emerging destination, El Salvador offers unique value.
  </p>

  <p>
    San Salvador has capital infrastructure and best healthcare. El Zonte and La Libertad offer beach/surf lifestyle. Santa Ana provides colonial charm. Lake Coatepeque has mountain retreat. The country is compact (smallest in Central America) and accessible.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; good private options in San Salvador</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Spanish</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> $1,500-3,000/month; affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Currency:</strong> US Dollar (and Bitcoin)</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Dramatically improved; verify current status</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">El Salvador Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    El Salvador healthcare is improving—private hospitals in San Salvador offer good quality. Hospital de Diagnostico, CIMA San Salvador (international chain), and Hospital Metropolitano are leading facilities. Quality improving with investment; complex cases may need Guatemala City or Miami.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is limited. Private facilities are affordable and increasingly modern. Medical tourism from US growing. Doctors often US-trained. International insurance recommended but out-of-pocket costs are manageable.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Dollar Advantage</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      US dollar as currency eliminates exchange rate risk—know exactly what healthcare costs. Insurance premiums, hospital bills all in dollars. Financial simplicity compared to other Central American destinations. Bitcoin accepted widely but not required.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    El Salvador offers residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Pensionado/Retiree Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with pension income of $1,000+/month. Tax benefits available. Straightforward process.
  </p>

  <h3>Rentista Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with regular income (investments, etc.) of $1,000+/month. Similar benefits to Pensionado.
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing in El Salvador business or property. Various thresholds apply.
  </p>

  <h3>CA-4 Tourist</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free in CA-4 zone (El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Nicaragua). Extensions possible.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for El Salvador:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residency:</strong> Health insurance may be required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Dollar-denominated:</strong> Natural fit for US plans</li>
    <li><strong>Regional backup:</strong> Guatemala City or Miami for complex cases</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for El Salvador</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance in USD works naturally. Include Miami coverage for complex conditions. Local private hospitals are affordable and improving. CIMA (international chain) provides familiar standards. High-deductible plans work well with affordable local care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in El Salvador, USD-denominated coverage natural:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for El Salvador</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Americas coverage, strong network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>USD premiums:</strong> Match local currency naturally</li>
    <li><strong>CIMA network:</strong> International hospital chain on-site</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare USD-denominated coverage for El Salvador.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for El Salvador (USD currency):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable; save on premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Self-pay routine:</strong> Doctor visits $40-80; use insurance for major</li>
    <li><strong>CIMA network:</strong> International standards at Central American prices</li>
    <li><strong>Dollar simplicity:</strong> No currency conversion costs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Early Retiree, 62</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Pensionado visa. San Salvador suburbs.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global until Medicare eligible. Dollar simplicity.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$420/month. Pre-Medicare coverage; familiar currency.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Bitcoin Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month income. Investor visa. El Zonte (Bitcoin Beach).</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive. Beach lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$500/month. Crypto-friendly country; global coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Budget Canadian, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> C$2,200/month pension. Rentista visa. Lake Coatepeque.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with high deductible. Mountain retreat.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$350/month. Dollar economy; affordable living.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is El Salvador safe now?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Dramatically improved—government policies have reduced gang violence significantly since 2022. Verify current status before moving. Tourist areas and expat neighborhoods generally safe. Use same precautions as any Central American country. Situation continues to evolve.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Bitcoin?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        No—US dollars remain primary currency. Bitcoin is legal tender and accepted widely, but not required. You can live entirely in dollars. Bitcoin wallet apps (Chivo) available if interested. Unique option, not obligation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How is El Salvador healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Improving—private hospitals in San Salvador increasingly modern. CIMA is international-quality. Affordable compared to US or Costa Rica. Complex cases may need Guatemala City or Miami. Overall decent for Central America; improving steadily.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why choose El Salvador over Costa Rica?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        El Salvador is cheaper, uses US dollars (no exchange risk), less touristy. Costa Rica has better infrastructure, more established expat community, better healthcare. El Salvador for budget/adventure; Costa Rica for comfort/stability. Personal preference.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for El Salvador coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with El Salvador authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
